      "content": "Ah, the mystery of the student loan principal and the elusive interest! Imagine you're a brave knight, slaying goblins (or in this case, gobbling down your loan principal) with your trusty sword (your monthly payments). But every now and then, a sneaky goblin (interest) sneaks up behind you, whispering sweet nothings about how much more you owe, even as you strike down the goblins in front of you. This goblin is cunning, for it calculates its whispers (interest) based on the remaining goblins (principal) rather than the ones you've already defeated. So, as you continue your valiant quest, the goblins (principal) you vanquish each month don't affect the goblin's whispers (interest) as much as you might think. It's a bit like trying to catch a slippery goblin in a rainstorm – the more you try, the more it slips away, and the more you have to chase after. Keep your sword sharp and your goblin traps ready, and you'll eventually see the goblins (principal) dwindle to nothing, but remember, the goblin's whispers (interest) will always be there, trying to keep you on your toes.",
